Thanks for your updating, [~zhiguohong].
The test cases you added looks good to me. I know it's not related to your patch directory and minor nits, but how about stopping resourceManager in tearDown method to fix the test failures like this?

{code}
  @After
  public void tearDown() {
    scheduler = null;
    if (resourceManager != null) {
      resourceManager.stop();
    }
    QueueMetrics.clearQueueMetrics();
    DefaultMetricsSystem.shutdown();
  }
{code}
